HEADWORD: Metage
<hw>Met"age</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Mete</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Measurement,
especially of coal.</def> <rj><au>De Foe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Charge for, or price of, measuring.</def>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metagenesis</ent>⟦br⟧
